WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:37.040 --> 00:00:39.040
 Oh my God! 

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:45.360
 -Jason! 
 -Do you know him? 

00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:47.440
 Yeah, his name is Jason O'Connor. 

00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:50.120
 Don't move Jason, don't move. 

00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:56.040
 What time will you be ready? 

00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:58.080
 Around 5 o'clock. 

00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:00.040
 Hey, don't be late. 

00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:02.120
 I won't. 

00:01:03.720 --> 00:01:06.520
 Hey! What are you looking at? 

00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:10.680
 Hey, if I see you sniffing 
 around Caitríona again I'll..! 

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:13.040
 Leave me be for God's sake! 

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:15.120
 Leave you be? 

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:19.880
 I lost my job and Berni because 
 of this crap! Is that not enough? 

00:01:19.960 --> 00:01:22.040
 Well, poor old you! 

00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:26.840
 What else do you expect when you mess
 around with another man's woman? 

00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:29.840
 Vince, I wasn't on my own 
 when it happened. 

00:01:29.920 --> 00:01:32.520
 Or have you forgotten? 

00:01:36.880 --> 00:01:39.080
 You look very happy with yourself. 

00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:41.560
 I've just got great news! 

00:01:41.640 --> 00:01:43.640
 Oh? What is it? 

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.120
 Well..! 

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:49.120
 Can I have 4 take-away coffees? 
 The machine is broken again. 

00:01:49.200 --> 00:01:51.200
 One minute, Caitríona. 

00:01:51.280 --> 00:01:53.280
 Róise, do you want a coffee? 

00:01:53.360 --> 00:01:56.960
 No, it's alright. 
 I just had one. See you there. 

00:01:57.040 --> 00:01:58.640
 Bye. 

00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:04.880
 Whatever it is, it can't be that bad.

00:02:04.960 --> 00:02:07.680
 -Oh, hi Caitríona. 
 -Do you mind? 

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:13.160
 So, any news? 

00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:15.240
 I had a date with Ciarán last night. 

00:02:15.320 --> 00:02:17.200
 That's great! 

00:02:17.280 --> 00:02:19.240
 It didn't go very well. 

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:20.560
 Why? 

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:24.240
 Kelly isn't very happy about it. 

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:26.320
 What has he got to do with it? 

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:30.000
 He could create problems for me 
 as regards my work. 

00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:31.880
 Really? 

00:02:32.280 --> 00:02:35.880
 The only thing that's bothering 
 that man is jealousy. 

00:02:35.960 --> 00:02:39.160
 You're not going to let him 
 ruin everything, are you? 

00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:44.560
 Come on, it's over between you. 
 He has to accept that. 

00:02:45.560 --> 00:02:48.080
 That's if you're still interested 
 in Ciarán. 

00:02:48.160 --> 00:02:50.960
 -Of course I am. 
 -And he's interested in you? 

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:54.040
 That's what he says anyway. 

00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:57.720
 Right, there's no problem then. 
 Forget about Kelly. 

00:02:57.800 --> 00:03:00.040
 It's a pity it's not that simple. 

00:03:00.120 --> 00:03:03.520
 Go for it before he's snatched up 
 by some other woman. 

00:03:03.600 --> 00:03:06.760
 It won't take a fine thing like him 
 too long! 

00:03:09.240 --> 00:03:12.280
 -Come on Jason! 
 -What's the matter with him? 

00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:16.240
 We found him collapsed at the 
 graveyard. I think he's just drunk. 

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:18.320
 Jason are you alright? 

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:21.800
 You stay out of this. 
 You've done enough damage as it is. 

00:03:21.880 --> 00:03:24.880
 Come on Jason. Lord above! 

00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:28.400
 -We'd better take him to hospital. 
 -What's wrong with him? 

00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:30.880
 It's probably just the effects 
 of drink. 

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:34.600
 But I'm worried about the vomiting 
 as he has a head injury. 

00:03:34.680 --> 00:03:37.480
 -This is your fault you wretch! 
 -Come on Jason. 

00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:40.160
 I'll take him to the hospital, 
 he's my son! 

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:42.440
 Declan knows what he's doing, okay? 

00:03:42.520 --> 00:03:45.320
 Alright, but I'm going with you. 

00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:47.800
 -Alright. 
 -I'll ring you later. 

00:03:47.880 --> 00:03:50.680
 Maybe you should take 
 your friend home, Ríona. 

00:03:50.760 --> 00:03:51.760
 Okay. 

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:53.840
 I want to be by myself! 

00:03:57.080 --> 00:03:59.680
 Toasted special. 

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:01.240
 Berni? 

00:04:01.320 --> 00:04:03.320
 That's all you wanted, isn't it? 

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:05.600
 Yes. 

00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:12.960
 God only knows how many men 
 that woman has gone through! 

00:04:13.040 --> 00:04:14.840
 It's true. 

00:04:14.920 --> 00:04:19.240
 Do you know anyone else who has been 
 married and separated twice? 

00:04:19.320 --> 00:04:22.120
 Not to mention all the boyfriends 
 she's had. 

00:04:22.200 --> 00:04:26.080
 As for poor little Evan, he doesn't 
 know if he's coming or going... 

00:04:26.160 --> 00:04:30.360
 ..with all the fathers 
 he's had since he was born. 

00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:32.480
 Sarah, please. 

00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:36.360
 She had better be careful 
 or she'll be left on the shelf. 

00:04:38.360 --> 00:04:42.960
 It doesn't give me any satisfaction 
 to know that I was right. 

00:04:44.440 --> 00:04:48.240
 -That Jason would leave. 
 -He wouldn't leave if he understood. 

00:04:48.320 --> 00:04:51.720
 I never intended to go ahead 
 with that silly deal. 

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:54.800
 Frig Tadhg anyway. 

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:59.080
 Listen, you're exhausted. Come home 
 and I'll cook you something. 

00:04:59.160 --> 00:05:03.360
 I don't understand why he told him. 
 What did he have to gain from it? 

00:05:03.440 --> 00:05:06.240
 It looks as bad for him 
 as it does for me. 

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:09.520
 I can't make head nor tail 
 of that man. 

00:05:09.600 --> 00:05:14.200
 I never thought he'd endanger his 
 relationship with Jason in that way. 

00:05:14.280 --> 00:05:16.360
 Obviously he did. Let's go home. 

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:20.000
 Maybe he didn't. 

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:22.520
 What do you mean? 

00:05:23.160 --> 00:05:25.960
 Maybe someone else told him 
 about it. 

00:05:26.040 --> 00:05:28.080
 Don't torment yourself over this. 

00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:31.360
 Jason's gone now and 
 nothing can be done about it. 

00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:33.440
 You told him. 

00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:35.960
 He was going to leave you anyway. 

00:05:36.040 --> 00:05:38.440
 It's much better that he leave now...

00:05:38.520 --> 00:05:41.920
 ..rather than when 
 you had learned to trust him again. 

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:44.600
 -I know it doesn't..! 
 -Shut up! 

00:05:44.680 --> 00:05:47.920
 I don't want to hear 
 another word from you! 

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:51.200
 You've ruined my life yet again! 
 Do you realise that? 

00:05:51.280 --> 00:05:55.640
 He was never good enough for you. 
 I did it for your benefit. 

00:05:55.720 --> 00:05:57.920
 For my benefit? For my benefit? 

00:05:58.040 --> 00:06:01.640
 Is that why you hit me as well? 
 For my own benefit? 

00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:04.720
 Don't start that again. 
 I didn't mean to do it..! 

00:06:04.800 --> 00:06:07.000
 You're sick! Do you understand that? 

00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:10.080
 Totally and utterly 
 out of your bleedin' mind! 

00:06:10.160 --> 00:06:13.760
 And I'm not going to let you 
 ruin my life anymore! 

00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:15.240
 Suzy! 

00:06:23.400 --> 00:06:25.200
 Sit down. 

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:28.880
 It's fine, I just wanted 
 to have a few words with you. 

00:06:28.960 --> 00:06:31.160
 Right, go on. 

00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:36.200
 I've been thinking 
 about what we said last night. 

00:06:36.280 --> 00:06:37.560
 Right. 

00:06:37.720 --> 00:06:42.400
 Well, this could have a huge effect 
 on my livelihood. 

00:06:42.480 --> 00:06:45.080
 And my job is very important to me. 

00:06:45.160 --> 00:06:48.360
 I know that and I understand, 
 really I do. 

00:06:49.680 --> 00:06:51.960
 I don't think you do. 

00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:05.280
 There are more important things 
 in life than work. 

00:07:05.360 --> 00:07:07.520
 Are you sure about this? 

00:07:07.600 --> 00:07:11.000
 I'm not going to let people 
 push me around anymore. 

00:07:11.080 --> 00:07:14.080
 I'll live my life the way I see fit 
 from now on. 

00:07:39.280 --> 00:07:41.440
 Sorry. 

00:07:41.520 --> 00:07:43.960
 -I have to answer this. 
 -Okay. 

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:46.120
 Hello. 

00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:49.400
 Yes. 

00:07:50.480 --> 00:07:52.480
 Of course, of course. 

00:07:52.960 --> 00:07:55.560
 I'll be over in a minute. Alright. 

00:07:56.520 --> 00:07:57.920
 Goodbye. 

00:07:59.360 --> 00:08:01.360
 Is everything alright? 

00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:03.480
 Yeah. Sorry, I have to go. 

00:08:03.960 --> 00:08:06.360
 Right, I'll see you tonight then? 

00:08:06.440 --> 00:08:08.840
 Definitely! Bye. 

00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:10.760
 Bye. 

00:08:11.840 --> 00:08:15.680
 Séamus, why won't you tell me 
 what's the matter with you? 

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:21.360
 Are you going to make the tea 
 or do I have to do it myself? 

00:08:21.440 --> 00:08:24.440
 Don't you realise 
 that I'm worried about you? 

00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:27.520
 If so, you're wasting your time. 

00:08:27.600 --> 00:08:32.640
 How can I help you when you 
 won't tell me what's wrong with you? 

00:08:33.920 --> 00:08:36.160
 I don't want your help. 

00:08:36.240 --> 00:08:38.640
 Telling you wouldn't help matters. 

00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:40.840
 Try me! 

00:08:40.920 --> 00:08:46.960
 For the love of God, tell me what 
 the hell is bothering you, Séamus. 

00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:49.760
 I'm losing my sight. 

00:08:52.240 --> 00:08:54.240
 I'm going blind. 

00:08:54.320 --> 00:08:56.920
 That's what's wrong. 

00:08:58.400 --> 00:09:01.600
 You're a great comfort to me. 

00:09:02.680 --> 00:09:07.160
 I just wish I had told you sooner. 
 Frig it! 

00:09:07.240 --> 00:09:09.240
 How do you know? 

00:09:11.800 --> 00:09:13.800
 What do you mean, how do I know? 

00:09:13.880 --> 00:09:17.080
 How do you know 
 that you're going blind? 

00:09:17.160 --> 00:09:19.160
 What kind of a question is that? 

00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:22.600
 It's a very reasonable question, 
 you know. 

00:09:23.800 --> 00:09:26.400
 I'm losing sight in both my eyes! 

00:09:26.480 --> 00:09:30.080
 When I strain them trying 
 to read those bloody forms... 

00:09:30.160 --> 00:09:32.160
 ..I get headaches. 

00:09:32.240 --> 00:09:35.040
 Then I get all flustered. 

00:09:35.120 --> 00:09:39.320
 Lord above, 
 we have to ring the doctor. 

00:09:41.520 --> 00:09:43.840
 Blast you and your doctors. 

00:09:43.920 --> 00:09:47.360
 No doctor can help me! 
 Once you start losing your sight... 

00:09:47.440 --> 00:09:50.640
 ..there's nothing you can do 
 about it and that's that. 

00:09:51.320 --> 00:09:53.120
 Good God! 

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:57.000
 -Ríona. 
 -Daniel. 

00:09:57.120 --> 00:09:59.560
 I'm looking for Suzy. Is she here? 

00:09:59.640 --> 00:10:01.040
 No. 

00:10:01.120 --> 00:10:05.120
 -Do you know where she is? 
 -I have no idea. 

00:10:05.200 --> 00:10:07.600
 She was upset earlier. 

00:10:07.680 --> 00:10:09.680
 Really? Why? 

00:10:09.760 --> 00:10:12.560
 You know, Jason and everything. 

00:10:13.920 --> 00:10:16.920
 -Right. 
 -I'm very worried about her. 

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:21.040
 Well if I see her, 
 I'll be sure to tell her. Okay? 

00:10:23.080 --> 00:10:24.480
 Right. 

00:10:25.400 --> 00:10:27.960
 Goodbye. 

00:10:35.800 --> 00:10:37.800
 Well, he's gone. 

00:10:37.880 --> 00:10:39.880
 What did he say? 

00:10:39.960 --> 00:10:42.400
 Just that he's worried about you. 

00:10:44.280 --> 00:10:47.080
 Are you sure you want 
 to do this Suzy? 

00:10:52.120 --> 00:10:53.520
 Yes. 

00:15:17.120 --> 00:15:19.000
 -Hiya. 
 -Hi Mack. 

00:15:19.080 --> 00:15:21.080
 So, any news? 

00:15:21.160 --> 00:15:25.440
 Yes, actually. Suzy has given 
 a statement against her father. 

00:15:25.520 --> 00:15:27.200
 Great! 

00:15:27.280 --> 00:15:30.440
 -You're happy about it, right? 
 -Yes, but..! 

00:15:30.520 --> 00:15:32.320
 But what? 

00:15:32.400 --> 00:15:36.120
 If we go ahead with this, chances are
 that Daniel will file charges... 

00:15:36.200 --> 00:15:38.800
 ..against you for your assault 
 on him. 

00:15:38.880 --> 00:15:41.600
 -I don't give a damn what he does. 
 -Seriously? 

00:15:42.160 --> 00:15:46.960
 If I have to do time in prison 
 so that he'll get his comeuppance... 

00:15:47.040 --> 00:15:48.880
 ..I'll do it. 

00:15:48.960 --> 00:15:51.960
 -Are you sure about that? 
 -Positive. 

00:15:52.040 --> 00:15:54.920
 Fair play sis. I'll see you later. 

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:57.600
 In a way, I believe him. 

00:15:58.520 --> 00:16:02.520
 Am I stupid to think that 
 after what he's done to me? 

00:16:03.240 --> 00:16:05.840
 He told you about it himself? 

00:16:06.520 --> 00:16:08.120
 Yes. 

00:16:08.200 --> 00:16:11.000
 And did you believe 
 what he had to say? 

00:16:11.080 --> 00:16:13.280
 Well, that's the thing. 

00:16:15.040 --> 00:16:16.840
 I don't know. 

00:16:18.800 --> 00:16:23.720
 Máire, how did you and Peadar manage 
 to stay together all these years? 

00:16:23.800 --> 00:16:27.000
 Peadar and I had 
 our fair share of problems. 

00:16:28.280 --> 00:16:33.280
 And they weren't your average 
 ups and downs either. 

00:16:34.920 --> 00:16:37.720
 They were much more serious 
 than that. 

00:16:38.720 --> 00:16:42.720
 Máire, Peadar didn't do something 
 like that to you, did he? 

00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:46.680
 Peadar didn't do anything. 

00:16:46.760 --> 00:16:49.200
 You have to make up your own mind. 

00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:53.760
 You have to think of yourself 
 and Evan. 

00:16:54.360 --> 00:16:59.360
 And above all else, you have to ask 
 yourself whether you have enough... 

00:16:59.440 --> 00:17:04.400
 ..love in your heart for Rory to be 
 able to forgive him for what he did. 

00:17:06.920 --> 00:17:08.920
 I knew it! 

00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:10.600
 Indeed! 

00:17:10.680 --> 00:17:15.200
 I told you that you weren't going 
 blind but you wouldn't believe me. 

00:17:16.200 --> 00:17:19.800
 Where are they? 
 Take them out and put them on. 

00:17:19.880 --> 00:17:23.080
 Or before long you'll be blind 
 for certain! 

00:17:31.040 --> 00:17:33.040
 Was I not right all along? 

00:17:33.680 --> 00:17:37.080
 After telling me 
 that I had lost the plot! 

00:17:38.480 --> 00:17:41.280
 You have me spoiled, you know. 

00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:43.360
 I know darling. 

00:17:43.440 --> 00:17:45.640
 So, how was work today? 

00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:47.320
 Crazy. 

00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:49.760
 You must miss Rory. 

00:17:51.400 --> 00:17:54.000
 Because of the work load, I mean. 

00:17:54.720 --> 00:17:57.720
 We're busy but we're coping 
 without him. 

00:17:58.080 --> 00:18:00.120
 Look, I'm sorry darling. 

00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:03.200
 I didn't mean 
 to make you feel uncomfortable. 

00:18:03.800 --> 00:18:05.800
 It's alright. 

00:18:07.360 --> 00:18:09.960
 Mack attacked Daniel a while back. 

00:18:10.040 --> 00:18:14.280
 That's the reason 
 why Mack had to leave for a while. 

00:18:14.360 --> 00:18:17.960
 Daniel has been threatening 
 to file charges since then. 

00:18:18.040 --> 00:18:20.560
 And if he does..! 

00:18:20.640 --> 00:18:22.640
 It won't look very good for you. 

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:24.120
 No. 

00:18:24.200 --> 00:18:28.200
 And if Kelly says anything about us 
 on top of that..! 

00:18:30.680 --> 00:18:32.600
 I see. 

00:18:32.680 --> 00:18:34.880
 That's not what I mean. 

00:18:36.160 --> 00:18:38.160
 Are you sure about that? 

00:18:42.440 --> 00:18:45.840
 Look, I understand your situation 
 Oonagh. 

00:18:47.200 --> 00:18:49.800
 It's your choice, okay? 

00:18:50.560 --> 00:18:52.560
 Yeah, I know. 

00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:56.800
 Thanks love, dinner was delicious. 

00:18:56.880 --> 00:18:58.880
 We aim to please! 

00:18:58.960 --> 00:19:02.560
 Besides, I have to prove 
 that I'm worth having around. 

00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:07.920
 What's the matter? 

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:11.400
 Come on Caitríona. 
 I was only joking. 

00:19:12.600 --> 00:19:15.400
 This is not going to work Vince. 

00:19:18.400 --> 00:19:20.400
 What have I done? 

00:19:20.880 --> 00:19:24.120
 Even with Rory gone 
 from the radio station... 

00:19:24.200 --> 00:19:26.200
 ..you're jealous. 

00:19:26.960 --> 00:19:29.000
 Jesus, of course I'm jealous! 

00:19:29.080 --> 00:19:31.880
 You slept with him, 
 for crying out loud! 

00:19:31.960 --> 00:19:34.960
 Can you hear the anger 
 in your voice? 

00:19:35.160 --> 00:19:37.560
 You can't let it go. 

00:19:38.280 --> 00:19:40.280
 Give me a chance. 

00:19:40.360 --> 00:19:42.360
 I'm working on it. 

00:19:42.440 --> 00:19:44.560
 That's the problem. 

00:19:44.880 --> 00:19:47.680
 That I'm trying to put it behind me? 

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:50.400
 Isn't that what you wanted? 

00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:52.400
 Yes. 

00:19:52.760 --> 00:19:54.960
 But you're going overboard. 

00:19:55.040 --> 00:19:57.040
 Wine, dinner. 

00:19:57.760 --> 00:20:02.280
 Waiting for me to get back from work 
 as if I were a schoolgirl. 

00:20:04.160 --> 00:20:06.760
 I'm doing my best, Caitríona. 

00:20:09.440 --> 00:20:11.240
 I know. 

00:20:12.520 --> 00:20:14.520
 So what's the problem? 

00:20:17.720 --> 00:20:19.720
 You can't do it, Vince. 

00:20:21.200 --> 00:20:24.600
 You can't forgive me 
 and you might never be able to. 

00:20:24.680 --> 00:20:28.280
 Thanks very much 
 for the vote of confidence. 

00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:33.320
 I'm sorry. 

00:20:35.080 --> 00:20:38.480
 Caitríona, we can get through this. 

00:20:40.480 --> 00:20:42.480
 I'm willing to give it a shot. 

00:20:44.040 --> 00:20:45.840
 Aren't you? 

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:50.960
 There's nothing I'd like more. 

00:20:51.040 --> 00:20:53.040
 But I just don't know Vince. 

00:20:55.320 --> 00:21:00.080
 If you can't let it go, 
 is it worth the effort? 

00:21:03.440 --> 00:21:05.440
 Another one. 

00:21:05.800 --> 00:21:08.600
 Do you think your kidneys 
 are up to it? 

00:21:09.680 --> 00:21:11.680
 Aisling, another one please. 

00:21:26.800 --> 00:21:30.400
 -The craic is about to begin! 
 -For God's sake Mam, stop! 

00:21:33.680 --> 00:21:37.080
 Look, I hate what I've done 
 to you. 

00:21:38.400 --> 00:21:41.400
 I can't believe 
 that I've hurt you in this way. 

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:46.680
 I know that nothing I say 
 will change what happened. 

00:21:46.760 --> 00:21:48.760
 No Rory, it won't. 

00:21:50.080 --> 00:21:54.880
 All the same, I think that 
 we should give it another try. 

00:21:57.280 --> 00:21:59.280
 Really? 

00:21:59.360 --> 00:22:00.680
 Really. 

00:22:00.760 --> 00:22:04.080
 Six months in Slovenia! 
 I'd be mad not to do it. 

00:22:04.160 --> 00:22:06.160
 What about your job here? 

00:22:06.400 --> 00:22:11.200
 I'm going to ask Labhrás 
 if I can take a career break. 

00:22:11.920 --> 00:22:15.480
 A career break? After all the time 
 you've taken off already! 

00:22:15.600 --> 00:22:17.600
 You don't have a hope, Róise. 

00:22:17.680 --> 00:22:20.560
 I'm going to ask Caitríona 
 to ask him on my behalf. 

00:22:20.640 --> 00:22:22.640
 Caitríona? Well good luck! 

00:22:23.760 --> 00:22:26.160
 Two bottles of lager please. 

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:29.040
 Actually not for me. 

00:22:29.120 --> 00:22:31.160
 -Why not? 
 -I have to go. 

00:22:31.680 --> 00:22:33.480
 What's up? 

00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:36.360
 Suzy is a bit upset. 
 I have to meet her. 

00:22:36.440 --> 00:22:38.240
 Oh great. 

00:22:38.320 --> 00:22:41.640
 -I'll talk to you tomorrow. 
 -Yeah, tomorrow. 

00:22:51.120 --> 00:22:54.920
 Mr. McLoughlin, I'd be grateful 
 if you would accompany me... 

00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:57.760
 ..to the station to answer 
 a few questions. 

00:22:59.120 --> 00:23:01.200
 Now, if you don't mind. 

00:23:01.280 --> 00:23:03.280
 Clear off good woman. 

00:23:03.360 --> 00:23:05.800
 As I said, I'd be grateful if..! 

00:23:05.880 --> 00:23:11.200
 I heard you and I gave you my answer.
 Now leave me be or you'll be sorry. 

00:23:12.360 --> 00:23:14.760
 I will not repeat myself. 

00:23:15.600 --> 00:23:18.800
 When do you intend stopping 
 this nonsense? 

00:23:18.880 --> 00:23:22.280
 There are laws to protect people 
 from this kind of thing. 

00:23:22.360 --> 00:23:25.960
 With you harassing me 
 and your brother attacking me... 

00:23:26.040 --> 00:23:29.640
 ..what exactly has the O Riain 
 family got against me? 

00:23:40.360 --> 00:23:42.560
 Do you want me to move out? 

00:23:44.720 --> 00:23:46.120
 Right. 

00:23:48.240 --> 00:23:51.840
 Caitríona, I don't want to lose 
 what we have. 

00:23:54.920 --> 00:23:56.920
 Neither do I. 

00:23:58.600 --> 00:24:02.600
 But I'm afraid that 
 it has already been lost. 

00:24:07.680 --> 00:24:09.680
 Vince, please! 

00:24:09.760 --> 00:24:12.160
 This is hard enough. 

00:24:15.480 --> 00:24:16.880
 Right. 

00:24:17.840 --> 00:24:19.640
 I'm sorry. 

00:24:20.800 --> 00:24:22.600
 Me too. 

00:24:42.400 --> 00:24:44.400
 -Hi! 
 -Hi. 

00:24:45.800 --> 00:24:47.800
 This is a nice surprise. 

00:24:47.960 --> 00:24:50.320
 I didn't expect to see you again 
 today. 

00:24:52.200 --> 00:24:54.200
 What's the matter? 

00:24:54.280 --> 00:24:58.120
 I could have done without 
 the dramatics today, to be honest. 

00:24:58.200 --> 00:25:00.480
 I know, I'm sorry about that. 

00:25:01.320 --> 00:25:03.320
 It's not your fault. 

00:25:03.400 --> 00:25:06.840
 We have to be careful, 
 you understand that don't you? 

00:25:06.920 --> 00:25:09.400
 Yes, I do. 

00:25:09.480 --> 00:25:13.040
 I think they thought 
 you were just giving me a lift home.

00:25:13.120 --> 00:25:15.120
 Which was true. 

00:25:15.200 --> 00:25:17.800
 Come on, don't be like that! 

00:25:17.880 --> 00:25:20.600
 I have a lot to lose. 
 If Lillian finds out..! 

00:25:20.680 --> 00:25:24.680
 I don't want to be in a situation 
 where I won't see my family again. 

00:25:24.760 --> 00:25:26.640
 You understand that, don't you? 

00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:29.160
 Yes! You remind me often enough. 

00:25:31.040 --> 00:25:32.240
 Ríona! 

00:25:33.600 --> 00:25:35.600
 I'm sorry. 

00:25:35.680 --> 00:25:38.680
 I'm just sick of this pretence. 

00:25:38.760 --> 00:25:40.760
 You're not the only one. 

00:25:40.840 --> 00:25:45.040
 I know. I'll tell her soon. 
 It's not the right time yet. 

00:25:45.120 --> 00:25:48.720
 It's you I want to be with. 
 You know that, don't you? 

00:25:56.680 --> 00:25:58.680
 What do you want? 

00:25:58.760 --> 00:26:02.080
 I signed a statement 
 against my father. 

00:26:03.760 --> 00:26:06.560
 -And? 
 -You said you'd stand by me. 

00:26:07.280 --> 00:26:10.480
 That's before I found out 
 that you sold my son. 

00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:13.080
 I never meant to go ahead with it. 

00:26:13.160 --> 00:26:16.160
 Why would I believe anything 
 you say? 

00:26:16.240 --> 00:26:18.880
 Ask Tadhg. I told him and Angela. 

00:26:18.960 --> 00:26:21.560
 That's easy to say. 

00:26:23.520 --> 00:26:27.320
 How did you think up such a thing 
 in the first place? 

00:26:27.400 --> 00:26:30.880
 I didn't think of it. 
 Tadhg came to me and threatened me. 

00:26:30.960 --> 00:26:33.960
 -Oh yeah. 
 -That's the truth. 

00:26:35.320 --> 00:26:37.720
 You're being very high and mighty...

00:26:37.800 --> 00:26:42.200
 ..about a baby you had no interest in
 until you found out he was dying. 

00:26:42.280 --> 00:26:45.480
 At least I didn't try 
 to friggin' sell him! 

00:26:45.680 --> 00:26:48.080
 Believe what you will. 

00:26:49.160 --> 00:26:51.560
 But I'm telling the truth. 

00:26:54.600 --> 00:26:56.920
 I did what you asked of me. 

00:26:58.320 --> 00:27:00.920
 I chose you over my father. 

00:27:01.560 --> 00:27:06.720
 I hope it's not too late for you 
 to stand by me, like you promised. 

00:27:11.800 --> 00:27:14.400
 You're still here I see, Daniel? 

00:27:14.480 --> 00:27:16.840
 Why wouldn't I be? 

00:27:16.920 --> 00:27:19.520
 I don't know. A pint, Tadhg. 

00:27:24.160 --> 00:27:26.160
 Maybe the game's not over after all.

00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:32.840
 Daniel McLoughlin, I'm arresting you
 under Section 3..! 

00:27:32.920 --> 00:27:34.920
 What the hell are you doing? 

00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:38.800
 Of the Non-Fatal Offences 
 Against the Person Act, 1997. 

00:27:38.880 --> 00:27:41.920
 What kind of nonsense is this, 
 woman? 

00:27:42.000 --> 00:27:47.120
 For the attack you carried out on 
 Suzy McLoughlin on April 15th 2004. 

00:27:47.200 --> 00:27:51.200
 -Don't be stupid, I didn't do that! 
 -You have a right to remain silent. 

00:27:51.280 --> 00:27:54.880
 Whatever you say may be taken down 
 and used against you. 

00:27:54.960 --> 00:27:57.560
 -You can't do this! 
 -Go ahead. 

00:27:57.640 --> 00:27:59.640
 Stop it! Stop it I said! 

00:28:01.160 --> 00:28:05.240
 Go ahead and enjoy the show 
 but you won't get away with it! 

00:28:05.320 --> 00:28:09.920
 Do you really think that you can 
 convict me of something I didn't do?

00:28:10.000 --> 00:28:13.200
 -And for which you have no evidence! 
 -I have evidence. 

00:28:13.280 --> 00:28:15.800
 What kind of bloody evidence? 

00:28:15.880 --> 00:28:20.200
 Your daughter made a statement saying
 that you attacked her that night. 

00:28:20.480 --> 00:28:22.080
 Jesus! 

00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:26.200
 It's all lies 
 and well you know it! 

00:28:26.280 --> 00:28:28.280
 Take him out, lads. 

00:28:28.360 --> 00:28:31.360
 Suzy! How could you do this to me? 

00:28:31.440 --> 00:28:32.840
 Suzy! 

00:28:32.920 --> 00:28:36.120
 What did I do to you to deserve this?

